The L'RAS [Association Sante Reunion) has published its weekly
report: dengue - one case.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This case occurred in a mixed dengue and chikungunya virus outbreak.
Both viruses are transmitted by the same _Aedes_ mosquito vector.
This report does not specify if the case was imported or locally
acquired. Although just one case, given the ongoing chikungunya virus
transmission, additional dengue virus transmission would not be surprising.

A map showing the location of Reunion Island in the Indian Ocean can
