[5] Mayotte
Date: Wed 5 May 2010
Source: Institut de Veille Sanitaire, Synthese Epidemiologique No. 5
[in French, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.invs.sante.fr/surveillance/dengue/territoires_ultramarins/2010/pe_dengue_chik_territoires_ultrmarins_07052010.pdf>


Cases of dengue 3 [virus infection] have been diagnosed on Mayotte
since 10 Mar 2010. As of 5 May 2010, 27 confirmed cases (15 imported
and 5 locally acquired), 7 under investigation and 11 probable cases
(9 locally acquired and 2 imported) have been identified. No serious
cases have been identified.

